# ─── Dependencies & build artifacts ──────────────────────────────────
# `node_modules` only matches the context root; `**/node_modules` is needed to
# catch nested copies (e.g. a stray `.next/node_modules/@prisma/client-<hash>`,
# whose transient files otherwise race the COPY checksum and fail the build).
node_modules
**/node_modules
.next
.output
.vinxi
.tanstack
dist-server
.pnpm-store
# Deploy state written on the HOST by deploy.sh (the content-hash file + the
# build-timing progress log). Not part of the image — and critically, the
# progress log is appended DURING the build via `tee`, so leaving .deploy/ in the
# context makes the sequential supervisor→web builds see DIFFERENT contexts,
# busting the `COPY --exclude=go-services . .` cache and rebuilding the expensive
# vite stage a second time. (`deploy` further down excludes the deploy/ SOURCE
# dir — a different name; this dot-prefixed state dir needs its own entry.)
.deploy

# ─── Version control ────────────────────────────────────────────────
.git
.gitignore

# ─── Environment files (injected at runtime, not baked into image) ──
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# ─── Security ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.pem

# ─── Dev / editor files ─────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
.vscode
.claude
.venv
coverage
.rmhbot-worktrees

# ─── Docker files (no recursion) ────────────────────────────────────
Dockerfile
Dockerfile.*
docker-compose*.yml
.dockerignore

# ─── CLI sub-package ────────────────────────────────────────────────
cli/dist
cli/node_modules

# ─── DB artifacts ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
db/avatars
db/builds
db/music

# ─── Heavy static media served from object storage / R2 (not the image) ─────
# /library, /music, /models and /sprites live in the S3-compatible bucket
# (MinIO → R2) behind cdn.rmhstudios.com — served on the web side via the TS
# asset() helper (see lib/storage/asset.ts) and on the deployed fleet by the Go
# `assets` service (go-services/internal/assets). Not off disk, not from the
# Node image — the host checkout is only the sync source (make assets-sync /
# scripts/sync-static-assets-to-r2.mjs). Keeping them out shrinks the build
# context, the COPY public layer, the build cache, AND the runtime image.
#   - music/sprites: excluded entirely.
#   - library: only the heavy PDFs (~488 MB) are excluded; covers/ stays so the
#     metadata step can see them. data/library-metadata.json (committed) carries
#     the catalogue. Adding a NEW library PDF requires running
#     `pnpm run library:metadata` locally and committing its cover + the JSON.
#   - models: still shipped IN the image for now (~20 MB; the Dockerfile
#     smoke-tests public/models/marlonjack.glb). Exclusion deferred to Phase 4 —
#     see block below.
public/library/*.pdf
public/music
public/sprites

# ─── Host-only content seed material (not in the image) ─────────────────────
# content/blog/*.mdx + content/news/*.mdx are untracked, host-only inputs to the
# one-off seed/migrate scripts (scripts/seed-news.ts, scripts/migrate-blogs.ts).
# Blog + news are served from the database at runtime, so nothing in the image
# reads content/ — and it isn't in the CI checkout, so baking it would fail the
# build. Bind-mount the host content/ into a one-shot container to run a seed
# script (the same pattern deploy.sh uses for public/).
content

# ── Assets/CDN cutover — Phase 4 (see docs/runbooks/go-backend-and-bazel.md) ──
# Uncomment these ONLY after /library and /models are served from the bucket by
# the Go assets service. Activating them drops ~500 MB from the build context.
# When you uncomment public/models, you MUST also remove the
# `test -f .../public/models/marlonjack.glb` sanity check in the Node Dockerfile
# (the file will no longer be in the build context).
# public/library
# public/models
public/**/*.psd
public/**/generate_sprites.py

# ─── Generated at build time (regenerated by build-vibe-packages) ───────────
# scripts/build-vibe-packages.ts rebuilds these during `vite build`, so shipping
# the host's generated copy in the context is pure waste (and risks staleness).
public/vibe-packages

# ─── Unused scripts ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
scripts/news-pipeline

# ─── Documentation ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
docs
*.md
!README.md

# ─── Go microservices fleet + new infra ──────────────────────────────
# go-services is included so the go-builder stage can compile supervisor,
# status, and bot-worker into /app/bin. Only deploy/ and .github/ are
# excluded from the context (they are never needed inside the image).
deploy
.github

# ─── Testing ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
testing
specs
vitest.config.ts
